ank (TV series)|Music Bank]]'' ([[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]])\n| March 27, 2015\n|-\n| ''[[Inkigayo]]'' ([[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]])\n| March 29, 2015\n|-\n| ''[[The Show (South Korean TV series)|The Show]]'' ([[SBS MTV]])\n| March 31, 2015\n|-\n| ''[[Show Champion]]'' ([[MBC Music]])\n| April 1, 2015\n|-\n| ''[[M Countdown]]'' ([[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]])\n| April 2, 2015\n|-\n| ''[[Show! Music Core]]'' ([[MBC TV]])\n| April 4, 2015\n|}\n\n==Release history==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| Region\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| Date\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| Format\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| Label\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| Various<ref name=\"iTunes Store\"/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=2| March 17, 2015\n| rowspan=2|[[Music download|Digital download]]\n| rowspan=2|[[SM Entertainment]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| South Korea\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|South Korea\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| March 18, 2015\n| [[Compact Disc|CD]]\n| SM Entertainment, [[KT Music]]\n|}\n\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Red Velvet}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ice Cream Cake}}\n[[Category:Red Velvet (band) EPs]]\n[[Category:2015 debut EPs]]\n[[Category:SM Entertainment EPs]]\n[[Category:Korean-language EPs]]\n[[Category:Dance-pop EPs]]\n[[Category:Concept albums]]\n", "name_user": "Quebec99", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixed references", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ice_Cream_Cake_(EP)"}
{"title_page": "Boles\u0142aw the Elder", "text_new": "{{ infobox nobility\n| name         = Boles\u0142aw the Elder\n| title        = Duke of Wielun, Niemodlin\n| image        = POL wojew\u00f3dztwo opolskie COA.svg\n| image_size   = 150px\n| caption      =  Coat-of-arms of Upper Silesia<br>(Cieszyn, Opole, Wielun, Niemondlin, etc)\n| noble family = [[Silesian Piasts]] of Opole\n| father       = [[Bolko I of Opole]]\n| mother       = Agnes (of Brandenburg?)\n| spouse       = Euphemia of Wroc\u0142aw\n| issue        = [[Boles\u0142aw II of Niemodlin|Boles\u0142aw II]]<br>[[Wenceslaus of Niemodlin]]<br>Margareta<br>Anna<br>Hedwig<br>[[Henry of Niemodlin]]<br>Judith<br>Elisabeth\n| birth_date   = c. 1293\n| birth_place  = \n| death_date   = c. 21 March 1365\n| death_place  = \n}}\n'''Boles\u0142aw the Elder''' ({{lang-pl|'''Boles\u0142aw Pierworodny'''}}; {{circa|1293}} &ndash; {{circa|21 March 1365}}), was a Silesian Duke.  He was the ruling Duke of [[Wielu\u0144]] during 1313\u20131326, Duke of [[Niemodlin]] from 1313 and ruler over [[Prudnik]] from 1336 until his death.\n\nHe was the eldest son of Duke [[Bolko I of Opole]] by his wife Agnes, probably a daughter of Margrave [[Otto III, Margrave of Brandenburg|Otto III of Brandenburg]]. Boles\u0142aw was nicknamed \"the Elder\" or \"First-born\" (''Pierworodny'') in order to distinguish him from his younger brother, who, for unknown reasons, was also named Boles\u0142aw (Bolko).\n\n==Life==\nAfter his father's death in 1313, Boles\u0142aw inherited the Duchies of [[Wielu\u0144]] and [[Niemodlin]]. Until 1323, he exercised the guardianship on behalf of his younger brothers, then too youngs for rule by their own. His political career was strongly connected with the [[House of Luxembourg]], rulers of [[Bohemia]]. This alliance with the Bohemian Kingdom caused a war between him and [[W\u0142adys\u0142aw I the Elbow-high]], which ended with the loss of Wielu\u0144 in 1326.\n\nOn 18 February 1327, together with the other Silesian Dukes, Boles\u0142aw paid homage to [[John I of Bohemia|King John of Bohemia]] in [[Opawa]]. One year later (in 1328) in order to fulfill his new responsibilities as vassal of Bohemian, he took part in the Crusade against the pagan [[Lithuania]]. After returning from this expedition, Boles\u0142aw follow his sovereign to [[Prague]], where he spent much time.\n\nIn 1336, as a reward for his faithful services, the King authorized Boles\u0142aw to buy the town of [[Prudnik]] with the surroundings villages by the amount of 2,000 fines.\n\nIn 1355 Boles\u0142aw took part in the trip of [[Charles IV, Holy Roman Emperor|King Charles of Bohemia]] to [[Rome]], where the latter was crowned [[Holy Roman Emperor]].\n\nBoles\u0142aw died between 1362 and 1365. His place of burial is unknown.\n\n==Marriage and issue==\nBy 29 November 1325, Boles\u0142aw married with Euphemia (b. ca. 1312 \u2013 d. 21 March aft. 1384), daughter of [[Henry VI the Good]], Duke of [[Wroc\u0142aw]]. They had eight children:\n#[[Boles\u0142aw II of Niemodlin|Boles\u0142aw II]] (b. 1326/35 \u2013 d. by 25 June 1368).\n#[[Wenceslaus of Niemodlin|Wenceslaus]] (b. 1336/46 \u2013 d. June 1369).\n#Margareta (b. bef. 1340 \u2013 aft. 12 July 1399), married bef. 1354 to Landgrave Ulrich II of [[Leuchtenberg]].\n#Anna (b. bef. 1342/44 \u2013 d. 8 May 1365), a nun at St. Klara, Wroc\u0142aw.\n#Hedwig (b. bef. 1345 \u2013 d. 13 February 1413), Abbess of St. Klara, Wroc\u0142aw (1379).\n#[[Henry of Niemodlin|Henry]] (b. by 1345 \u2013 d. 14 September 1382).\n#Judith (b. bef. 1346 \u2013 aft. October 1378), married by 4 August 1359 to Duke [[Nicholas II, Duke of Opava|Nicholas II]] of Opawa.\n#Elisabeth (b. 1347/50? \u2013 d. aft. 25 June 1366), a nun at St. Klara, Wroc\u0142aw.\n\n==References==\n*{{MLCC |warning=1 |url=http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/SILESIA.htm#BoleslawFalkenbergdied13621365 |title-date= |title= SILESIA|date=August 2012}}\n*{{cite web |last=Marek |first=Miroslav |url=http://genealogy.euweb.cz/piast/piast8.html#BF |title= Genealogy of the House of Piast |publisher= Genealogy.EU}}{{Self-published source|date=August 2012}}{{Better source|date=August 2012}}\n*[https://archive.is/20121217221929/http://wwperson.informatik.uni-erlangen.de/cgi-bin/l3/LANG=engl/F=Bolko@II.@Heinrich/N=v.Schlesien-Oppeln Genealogical database by Herbert Stoyan]\n*[http://www.poczet.com/opolscy.htm Genealogy of the Dukes of Opole]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-hou|[[House of Piast]]||{{circa|1293}}|{{circa|21 March}}|1365}}\n{{s-reg}}\n{{s-bef | before=[[Bolko I of Opole|Bolko I]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Dukes of Greater Poland|Duke of Wielu\u0144]]\n|years=1313\u20131326}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[W\u0142adys\u0142aw I the Elbow-high]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef | before=new creation}}\n{{s-ttl | title=[[Dukes of Silesia|Duke of Niemodlin]]|years=1313\u20131365}}\n{{s-aft | after=[[Boles\u0142aw II of Niemodlin|Boles\u0142aw II]]<br/> [[Wenceslaus of Niemodlin|Wenceslaus]]<br/> [[Henry of Niemodlin|Henry]]}}\n{{end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boleslaw the Elder}}\n[[Category:1290s births]]\n[[Category:1360s deaths]]\n[[Category:Piast dynasty]]\n[[Category:Dukes of Prudnik]]\n", "text_old": "{{ infobox nobility\n| name         = Boles\u0142aw the Elder\n| title        = Duke of Wielun, Niemodlin\n| image        = POL powiat strzelecki COA.svg\n| image_size   = 150px\n| caption      =  Coat-of-arms of Upper Silesia<br>(Cieszyn, Opole, Wielun, Niemondlin, etc)\n| noble family = [[Silesian Piasts]] of Opole\n| father       = [[Bolko I of Opole]]\n| mother       = Agnes (of Brandenburg?)\n| spouse       = Euphemia of Wroc\u0142aw\n| issue        = [[Boles\u0142aw II of Niemodlin|Boles\u0142aw II]]<br>[[Wenceslaus of Niemodlin]]<br>Margareta<br>Anna<br>Hedwig<br>[[Henry of Niemodlin]]<br>Judith<br>Elisabeth\n| birth_date   = c. 1293\n| birth_place  = \n| death_date   = c. 21 March 1365\n| death_place  = \n}}\n'''Boles\u0142aw the Elder''' ({{lang-pl|'''Boles\u0142aw Pierworodny'''}}; {{circa|1293}} &ndash; {{circa|21 March 1365}}), was a Silesian Duke.  He was the ruling Duke of [[Wielu\u0144]] during 1313\u20131326, Duke of [[Niemodlin]] from 1313 and ruler over [[Prudnik]] from 1336 until his death.\n\nHe was the eldest son of Duke [[Bolko I of Opole]] by his wife Agnes, probably a daughter of Margrave [[Otto III, Margrave of Brandenburg|Otto III of Brandenburg]]. Boles\u0142aw was nicknamed \"the Elder\" or \"First-born\" (''Pierworodny'') in order to distinguish him from his younger brother, who, for unknown reasons, was also named Boles\u0142aw (Bolko).\n\n==Life==\nAfter his father's death in 1313, Boles\u0142aw inherited the Duchies of [[Wielu\u0144]] and [[Niemodlin]]. Until 1323, he exercised the guardianship on behalf of his younger brothers, then too youngs for rule by their own. His political career was strongly connected with the [[House of Luxembourg]], rulers of [[Bohemia]]. This alliance with the Bohemian Kingdom caused a war between him and [[W\u0142adys\u0142aw I the Elbow-high]], which ended with the loss of Wielu\u0144 in 1326.\n\nOn 18 February 1327, together with the other Silesian Dukes, Boles\u0142aw paid homage to [[John I of Bohemia|King John of Bohemia]] in [[Opawa]]. One year later (in 1328) in order to fulfill his new responsibilities as vassal of Bohemian, he took part in the Crusade against the pagan [[Lithuania]]. After returning from this expedition, Boles\u0142aw follow his sovereign to [[Prague]], where he spent much time.\n\nIn 1336, as a reward for his faithful services, the King authorized Boles\u0142aw to buy the town of [[Prudnik]] with the surroundings villages by the amount of 2,000 fines.\n\nIn 1355 Boles\u0142aw took part in the trip of [[Charles IV, Holy Roman Emperor|King Charles of Bohemia]] to [[Rome]], where the latter was crowned [[Holy Roman Emperor]].\n\nBoles\u0142aw died between 1362 and 1365. His place of burial is unknown.\n\n==Marriage and issue==\nBy 29 November 1325, Boles\u0142aw married with Euphemia (b. ca. 1312 \u2013 d. 21 March aft. 1384), daughter of [[Henry VI the Good]], Duke of [[Wroc\u0142aw]]. They had eight children:\n#[[Boles\u0142aw II of Niemodlin|Boles\u0142aw II]] (b. 1326/35 \u2013 d. by 25 June 1368).\n#[[Wenceslaus of Niemodlin|Wenceslaus]] (b. 1336/46 \u2013 d. June 1369).\n#Margareta (b. bef. 1340 \u2013 aft. 12 July 1399), married bef. 1354 to Landgrave Ulrich II of [[Leuchtenberg]].\n#Anna (b. bef. 1342/44 \u2013 d. 8 May 1365), a nun at St. Klara, Wroc\u0142aw.\n#Hedwig (b. bef. 1345 \u2013 d. 13 February 1413), Abbess of St. Klara, Wroc\u0142aw (1379).\n#[[Henry of Niemodlin|Henry]] (b. by 1345 \u2013 d. 14 September 1382).\n#Judith (b. bef. 1346 \u2013 aft. October 1378), married by 4 August 1359 to Duke [[Nicholas II, Duke of Opava|Nicholas II]] of Opawa.\n#Elisabeth (b. 1347/50? \u2013 d. aft. 25 June 1366), a nun at St. Klara, Wroc\u0142aw.\n\n==References==\n*{{MLCC |warning=1 |url=http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/SILESIA.htm#BoleslawFalkenbergdied13621365 |title-date= |title= SILESIA|date=August 2012}}\n*{{cite web |last=Marek |first=Miroslav |url=http://genealogy.euweb.cz/piast/piast8.html#BF |title= Genealogy of the House of Piast |publisher= Genealogy.EU}}{{Self-published source|date=August 2012}}{{Better source|date=August 2012}}\n*[https://archive.is/20121217221929/http://wwperson.informatik.uni-erlangen.de/cgi-bin/l3/LANG=engl/F=Bolko@II.@Heinrich/N=v.Schlesien-Oppeln Genealogical database by Herbert Stoyan]\n*[http://www.poczet.com/opolscy.htm Genealogy of the Dukes of Opole]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-hou|[[House of Piast]]||{{circa|1293}}|{{circa|21 March}}|1365}}\n{{s-reg}}\n{{s-bef | before=[[Bolko I of Opole|Bolko I]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Dukes of Greater Poland|Duke of Wielu\u0144]]\n|years=1313\u20131326}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[W\u0142adys\u0142aw I the Elbow-high]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef | before=new creation}}\n{{s-ttl | title=[[Dukes of Silesia|Duke of Niemodlin]]|years=1313\u20131365}}\n{{s-aft | after=[[Boles\u0142aw II of Niemodlin|Boles\u0142aw II]]<br/> [[W